{{Quote|You can stand to see the Imperial flag reign across the galaxy?|[[Saw Gerrera]], to [[Jyn Erso]]|<ref name="Rogue One: A Star Wars Story">''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Imperial_Emblem.svg|thumb|right|200px|The Imperial crest was a modified version of the Republic crest.]]
The '''Imperial crest''',<ref name="RVG">''[[Star Wars Rebels: The Visual Guide]]''</ref> also referred to as the '''Imperial insignia''',<ref name="BMF 25">{{BuildFalconCite|25|Starship Fact File}}</ref> the '''Imperial logo''',<ref name="TSWB">''[[The Star Wars Book]]''</ref> or the '''Imperial Army crest''',<ref name="IT">{{EncyclopediaCite|Imperial Troops}}</ref> was the six-spoked symbol of the [[Galactic Empire]]. An adaptation of the [[Galactic Republic]]'s [[Republic crest|eight-spoked roundel]],<ref name="RVG" /> the Empire's omnipresent sigil<ref name="TSWB" /> adorned many things Imperial, from [[Imperial military uniforms|military uniforms]] and [[starship]]s to flags and [[propaganda]] [[Painting|posters]].<ref name="RVG" />

The spoked design of the insignia was likened to a cogwheel.<ref name="Mando19">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 19: The Convert}}</ref>

{{Imp-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Imperial insignia was designed by [[John Mollo]], who was the [[Wikipedia:Costume designer|costume designer]] for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. In the [[Ask Lobot|''Q&A'']] feature of the [[Star Wars Insider 98|ninety-eighth issue]] of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine, Mollo revealed that he based the Imperial insignia on shapes used in 18th century fortifications.<ref name="BS">{{InsiderCite|98|Ask Lobot|Q&A}}</ref>

